Hermod's architecture is unified:
```
Hermod (The AI Agent)
├── Brain (AI Core)
│   ├── 4 Specialized LLMs (imported from SyberCraft LLM repo)
│   ├── 1 Shared Reasoning LLM (with ALL SyberSuite Agents)
│   ├── Native Runa VM for optimal thinking
│   └── Continuous learning systems
└── Body (IDE Interface)
    ├── Eyes (Code editor & project explorer)
    ├── Voice (AI panel & chat interface)
    ├── Hands (Code generation & modification)
    └── Memory (Knowledge graph & context)
```

**Hermod's Role in SyberSuite**:
- **AI Architect & Developer**: Designs, builds, and optimizes other AI systems
- **Self-Improvement**: Continuously evolves its own architecture
- **Code Generation**: Produces sophisticated code across all languages
- **Documentation**: Automatically generates technical documentation
- **Testing Framework**: Develops comprehensive testing protocols

**Update Workflow**:
When updates are needed:
1. Agent requests update → Nemesis reviews (approve/deny/justify)
2. If approved → Odin plans update requisition
3. Odin → Hermod builds and tests
4. Hermod submits to Odin → Odin approves or requests changes
5. If approved → Nemesis final approval, backup, and deploy
6. If denied → Return to previous step with required changes